It was last seen in 2009. In the historical period, there were also Asian lions and Caspian tigers, but at the beginning of our era they were completely eradicated. A subspecies of the European bison, the Caucasian bison, died out in 1925. The last copy of the Caucasian elk was killed in 1810 There are a lot of invertebrate species in the Caucasus, for example, about 1000 species of spiders have been confirmed there so far [3].